item.title: [HIVE-17020] Aggressive RS dedup can incorrectly remove OP tree branch
item.description:
Suppose we have an OP tree like this:

     ...
      |
     RS[1]
      |
    SEL[2]
    /    \
SEL[3]   SEL[4]
  |         |
RS[5]     FS[6]
  |
 ...

When doing aggressive RS dedup, we'll remove all the operators between RS5 and RS1, and thus the branch containing FS6 is lost.
item.summary: Aggressive RS dedup can incorrectly remove OP tree branch

status.description: The issue is considered finished, the resolution is correct. Issues which are not closed can be reopened.

comments.comment: I think we can disable aggressive dedup if any parent of RS5 has more than one child, and leave it to the normal case.
This might be a DUP of HIVE-16100
gopalv yeah the v3 patch of HIVE-16100 has the changes I intend to make here. Marking this one as a dup.
lirui If you have test case for it, can you please share it. It will be good to add it as part of HIVE-16100 fix.

ashutoshc, the following query can reproduce the issue:

explain from (select key from src cluster by key) a
  insert overwrite table d1 select a.key
  insert overwrite table d2 select a.key cluster by a.key;

The insert to table d1 will be lost.
